## Description {#details}

A specialized result for the <code><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a43d65ba07f09dd4c0c13d551848cdc88">LoopAnalysisManagerFunctionProxy</a></code> which retains a <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loopinfo">LoopInfo</a></code> reference.

This allows it to collect loop objects for which analysis results may be cached in the <code><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a58dde534a0ea2a23cb6c779c5c283f75">LoopAnalysisManager</a></code>.

### invalidate() {#a75c73b4e1766a4a21df494320f1e8cde}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool llvm::LoopAnalysisManagerFunctionProxy::Result::invalidate (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &amp; F, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/preservedanalyses">PreservedAnalyses</a> &amp; PA, FunctionAnalysisManager::Invalidator &amp; Inv)</>}>
Handler for invalidation of the proxy for a particular function.

If the proxy, <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loopinfo">LoopInfo</a></code>, and associated analyses are preserved, this will merely forward the invalidation event to any cached loop analysis results for loops within this function.

If the necessary loop infrastructure is not preserved, this will forcibly clear all of the cached analysis results that are keyed on the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loopinfo">LoopInfo</a></code> for this function.
